```suggestion

```

nit:
```suggestion
  rw [← getElem_reverse l _ (by omega) (by omega)]
```

There is already an ambient `α` in the file
```suggestion

```
and throughout the diff.
This is a "non-terminal `simp`"; could you squeeze it using `simp?` or `simp_rw` instead?
OK, thanks.
Which tactic sequence will be considered as "non-terminal `simp`"? Does `simp; omega` also non-terminal?
Or `simp at hl; simp`
`simp; omega` is probably fine. `simp at hl; simp [hl]` is not.
